<div id="base-ops" class="slide step" data-x="0" data-y="0" data-z="0" data-rotate-x="0" data-scale="1">
    <p>
        <strong>Mathematical Morphology</strong> is a computer vision technique for the analysis and processing of
        geometrical structures.
    </p>
    <p>
        Operators of morphology are mostly a composition of <em>Dilation</em> and <em>Erosion</em> algorithms.
    </p>
    <div id="op-dilate">
        <div>
            <p>
                <strong>Grayscale dilation</strong> is defined by:
            </p>
            $$ (A \oplus B)(x) = \sup_{y \in B}[A(y) + B(x-y)] $$
        </div>
        <img src="<%= require(REPORT_IMAGES_DIR + 'dilation.png') %>">
    </div>
    <div id="op-erode">
        <div>
            <p>
                While <strong>erosion</strong> is:
            </p>
            $$ (A \ominus B)(x) = \inf_{y \in B}[A(y) + B(x-y)] $$
        </div>
        <img src="<%= require(REPORT_IMAGES_DIR + 'erosion.png') %>">
    </div>
</div>
